      "side": 1,
      "message": "tl;dr Not needed **in scheduler**, so avoid complexity.\n\nFor those who create new branches w/o extra commit, yes, gitiles poller of scheduler will issue a trigger, potentially resulting in a build, which IMO is either intended or at least tolerable.\nMost branching projects i know today, such as V8 and Chromium, do smth like this when creating a branch:\n\n    git co master\n    export $VERSION ./tools/update_version $VERSION_FILE\n    git commit -m \"$VERSION\"\n    git push origin HEAD:refs/branch-heads/$VERSION  # creates new branch\n\nThis will result in scheduler, upon discovery of new ref, triggering a build only this latest commit.",
